      "alt": "Conversation with Claude.\n\n> The insight that there is no global truth, only local truth - that there is no shared \"true world\" we can claim access to, only creations of truth through the building of worlds through sense and symbol - that the other people in my life are projections of my own beliefs about the world, not actual independent observers (at least verifiably) - is often taken to lead directly to solipsism, the repugnant claim that l am the only person who exists or experiences or is real.\nWhy, precisely, is this not so?\n\nBecause the inference from \"I cannot verify other minds from outside\" to \"therefore I am the only mind\" smuggles in exactly the global standpoint you just denied yourself.",
